		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">General Tips for under 20 Bards<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Aug 22nd 11:09 AM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96695697731196&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96695697731196&num=2&post=1&replyto=96695697731196"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96695697731196></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=374"><span id=Scholar>Sapper</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>26 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.88]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Sapper&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>In case you havent read ANY other posts here or at any other sites, I'll tell you one more time...<br>LEARN TO TWIST!!<br>I watched a 17 level bard a few weeks back, in the throne room in CB, I asked him what he was singing.&nbsp;&nbsp;He said Whistling Warsong.<br>Can you be any more dense?[p]<br>You should always be singing at least 2 songs in combat, three is the standard that you should aspire to achieve, 4 for those with high real life dexterity and great connections.<br>What you sing depends on three things, its a judgment call from there.<br><b>*</b>The First Consideration is your Party. Consider your party makeup.  Tank heavy?  Caster Heavy?  Do you have an Enchanter? Do you have a Cleric?  Tanks like the Buff songs (Anthem De arms, Heal, Guardian Rythms, the occasional Jig) if they have alot of Procing wpns, break out the old drums and sing Chant of Battle, it will boost dex and str.<br>Casters like you to be able to taunt Mobs off them, and you need to be ready to tank for them.  Heal, Whistling warsong, Anthem or Chant is fine.  If you feel froggy, and if the environment allows, use your COD, DDD, and Largos to really taunt the enemy.<br>But do NOT use those AOE songs if you have multiple pulls and an enchanter with you.  Your AOE songs (Except Largos) will break Mez, and you will be wasting the Enchanter's Mana, and making him useless.<br><b>*</b>The second consideration is the target.  What is the nature of your enemy?  Caster?  Then sing Elemental, or Purifying and Guardian rythms.  (Ele and Pur rythms dont stack with each other, but either will stack with Guardian).  Also, consider using the Lullaby to break thier casts, it may not mez, but it WILL break a casters concentration regularly.  Is your target a part of an organized community?  Will it run for help, or will help come to it fairly quickly?  If so, have Selo's on standby and use it to allow the Tanks to keep up with it and kill it, or to run like hell if daddy or mommy shows up to git you.<br>Are you fighting one Mob or Multiples?  Your AOE songs (if you dont have an enchanter) can be of great use against multiple mobs, but prepare to be aggroed on, a LOT ;o)<br><b>*</b>The third consideration is your environment.  How close are the other mobs?  AOE or no AOE?  Do you need SOW?(Indoor Dungeons)  How far away is the puller pulling from, and how far away is the zone?  Where does the nearest Ubermob spwan, (Dvinn, Griffin, HG, Avoket, Named Orc or Gnoll)<br>You want to be aware at all times what is going on around you.  At the mid teens, you have songs that will help out the party in nearly every environment, and every situation, but having them memmed and knowing when to sing them is all part of what makes the difference between good Barding and Bad.<br><b>*</b>Bottom line, Dont sing a self buff song in a group unless you are the primary tank.  Never EVER bellow in a group unless you are trying to kill a running mob, there is something better you can do than 11 damage a mob every once in while, trust me.  <br>You are a party animal, sing songs to help the group, not yourself.<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Sapper Diesalot, Radiant guild, Quellious Server.&nbsp;&nbsp;"Chuck Berry cant twist this good!"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Aug 28th 4:58 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96695697731196&num=2&post=1&replyto=96749629921486"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96749629921486></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Very good article, though I must say I disagree with the last piece of advice, regarding Brusco's...  As any bard knows, there's not always a good tank around to do the pulling, so who gets to be the main puller?  Yours truly, the platemail-wearing bard.  When you are the desgnated puller, and you are in a group with low healing potential (no clerics, and maybe one druid or paladin), I've found that twisting in more than one buff song can be suicidal...  (Especially if you're having to deal with Lament-resisting multi-mob pulls.)  When I find that I've pulled a heavy hitter (or more...), and twisting group-related songs is just digging myself a grave, I can sometimes simply switch to Brusco's and tone it down, so to speak.  This gives the party a chance to get the stragglers off you.  Once the mob aggro tones down a bit, I can then try twisting in the (admittedly more useful) group songs again.  This will not work in all situations, as the makeup of the group can drastically change the songs needed for group (and the bard's!) survival.<br>   One other thing that must be said about toning down aggro is the use of fisticuffs. Once again, it depends on the group makeup.  You will be doing less aggro on a single mob, but potentially more on the group of mobs if you have a full party.  This is particularly useful when with a good party that can dish damage out well, and in even portions.  (Large melee parties are a good example of this.  Mixing in a few casters for quick nukes and/or hybrids with healing/nukes/snares can be good too.)<br>   Like the earlier post mentioned, you're one of the ultimate group classes.  Make it your goal to help the group!  However, an overeager bard soon makes for a dead bard, and can leave the party short-handed in a dangerous dungeon!<br><br>Good journeys, and have fun!  A bard's life is full of challenge and excitement!</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
